@alazaro I should clarify that one of the explicit goals for this project is to limit outside dependencies: the intent is that it's easy to deploy, even in an environment without python package deployment infrastructure -- see [note on the home page](https://github.com/svanoort/pyresttest#what-is-it).  

The core dependencies are baked into most RPM-based distros (pycurl, python are used for yum), aside from pyyaml which has RPM installation.  

If it weren't for that goal, there are a number of libraries that could be leveraged (requests, for example, for all but benchmarks and more low-level tests).  One goal of the [extension infrastructure](https://github.com/svanoort/pyresttest/blob/master/extensions.md) is to enable pulling in additional functionality in a way that degrades gracefully in the absence of libraries.

